Key Match Events: Embiid missed his first five shots en route to shooting 2-for-11 — including making 1 of 5 three-pointers.
The Sixers missed seven consecutive shot attempts during a 13-0 run by the Knicks, which gave the Knicks an 89-75 lead with 8:14 to play.
Post-Match Reflections: He [Embiid] went a perfect 8-for-8 from the foul line.
‘He was certainly rusty. Conditioning I think showed up fairly early,’ coach Nick Nurse said.

‘It felt good,’ Embiid said of playing with George for the first time. ‘I thought tonight we got in a nice rhythm, which we need to keep doing. Like I said, my job is to let the game be easy for the other guys, setting screens, and getting them open. I am just trying to make the game more simple, especially as I am getting back and trying to feel more confident.’
Miscellaneous Highlights: Embiid finished with 13 points, three rebounds, five assists, one block, and two turnovers while playing just 26 minutes, 25 seconds due to a minutes restriction.
Paul George had his best game as a Sixer, finishing with 29 points, 10 rebounds, three assists, three steals, a block, and four turnovers.
The nine-time All-Star forward made 7 of 11 three-pointers.
Rookie guard Jared McCain had another solid scoring night, finishing with 23 points on 7-for-16 shooting. He made four three-pointers.
OG Anunoby led the Knicks with 24 points. Towns added 21 points, 13 rebounds, and six assists. while getting the best of Embiid. Josh Hart finished with 14 points, 12 rebounds, and 10 assists.
